 the only solution to the system of equations.</p><p>Choice A is incorrect. In the <span class=\"italic\">xy</span>-plane, a parabola and a line can intersect at no more than two points. Since the graph of the first equation is a parabola and the graph of the second equation is a line, the system cannot have more than 2 solutions. Choice B is incorrect. There is a single ordered pair <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x comma y\"></span> that satisfies both equations of the system. Choice D is incorrect because the ordered pair <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 comma negative 3\"></span> satisfies both equations of the system.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"
